Next, use the 'mutation catalyst' (ğŸ§¬) on this 'grown' item; its value will likely drop to negative or zero. Crucially, apply the 'mutation catalyst' *again* to this new 'mutant grown' item. This usually creates a 'super-mutant' item with a very high value (55-60). Once you achieve a 'super-mutant' item with a high positive value, **stop modifying it!** Applying tools to an already 'super-mutant' item, especially another 'mutation catalyst', will almost always 'corrupt' it and send its value plummeting into severe negatives. Avoid making items too complex with many components early on, as 'overcomplicated' hybrids are harder to manage and often lead to negative values.

message: Focus on using the ğŸŒ¡ï¸ growth serum on individual ingredients first, as it reliably creates positive value 'grown' items. Combining 'grown' items from the same environment (e.g., two land creatures) adds their values. message: Careful! Combining items to include all three environmental features (land, water, air) often creates 'overcomplicated' items with very negative values. The 'growth serum' is generally good for increasing value on simple ingredients and initial hybrids. The 'mutation catalyst' is a high-risk, high-reward tool; it can sometimes reverse highly negative values but often introduces 'mutant' or 'corrupted' features that severely decrease value. Aim for a good positive score with two environmental features (e.g., land and water) and submit, rather than risking a drop to 0 by trying to get all three.
